  "title": "Sales Manager (Marine Software)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct market research and analysis to identify new business opportunities and key growth segments</li>\n  <li>Build and expand a strong sales pipeline by developing relationships with potential clients</li>\n  <li>Drive conversion of leads into new customers and consistently achieve regional sales targets</li>\n  <li>Manage and strengthen customer relationships through proactive account management and solution-based engagement</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with Customer Success, Marketing, and Support teams to enhance customer satisfaction and product utilization</li>\n  <li>Respond to client requests promptly and ensure consistent service delivery</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve understanding of customers, competitors, and market dynamics to refine sales strategies</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date sales records, reports, and administrative tools as required</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Over 3 years of solid sales experience working with international clients and partners</li>\n  <li>Strong passion for the maritime, transport, and logistics industries</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Sales, Economics, or a related discipline (or equivalent experience)</li>\n  <li>Proven ability to work independently and thrive in a multicultural business environment</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation abilities</li>\n  <li>Highly proactive, results-driven, and resourceful in achieving targets</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical thinking with a strategic approach to market development</li>\n  <li>Exceptional planning, time management, and organizational skills</li>\n  <li>Proficient in writing and speaking; additional languages would be an advantage</li>\n</ul>",
